	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-10-05T07:05:05">Secure Income REIT Plc is a United Kingdom-based real estate investment trust (REIT). The Company is engaged in investing in real estate. The Company owns a portfolio of 28 assets. It properties comprises healthcare assets and leisure assets. The healthcare assets comprises 21 freehold private hospitals located throughout England, 20 of which are let to a subsidiary of Ramsay Health Care Limited and the other to Groupe Sinoue, a French mental health company. The leisure assets consist of five visitor attractions and two hotels, located in England and Germany. The Company's United Kingdom leisure asset includes Madame Tussauds London, Alton Towers theme park and the Alton Towers hotel, Thorpe Park theme park and Warwick Castle. The German assets include Heide Park theme park and the Heide Park hotel, both located in Soltau, Saxony. The Company's subsidiaries include SIR Theme Parks Limited, SIR ATH Limited, SIR Oaklands Limited and SIR Springfield Limited, among others.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-10-09T09:04:13">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Secure Income REIT PLC revenues totaled L52.9M. Net income totaled to L101.9M. Results are not comparable due to year end change.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
